itemDescription: Dean of Armagh, b. 21 December 1826, d. 2 January 1900

wikipedia_page.main: Augustine FitzGerald, D.D. (9 November 1827 – 2 January 1900) was Dean of Armagh from 1896 until his death.FitzGerald was educated at Trinity College, Dublin and ordained in 1852. He began his career with curacies at Stillorgan and Moneymore. He was Perpetual curate of Portadown from 1859 to 1896. He was Precentor of Armagh Cathedral from 1886 to 1896.

response: Augustine FitzGerald (1765 – 4 December 1834) was an Irish politician.  He was a Member of Parliament (MP) for Clare from 1808 to 1818, and as MP for Ennis briefly in early 1832.
